<TITLE> Body of Ruhul Amin arrives in Dhaka Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 6 (bdnews24.com)The body of Ruhul Amin, Bangladesh's ambassador to France, who died from brain haemorrhage in Paris, will reach Dhaka Tuesday, the foreign ministry said in a statement Sunday. The body will be flown to Bangladesh by an Emirates flight, which will reach Zia International Airport at 9.55am, the statement said. The first namaz-e-janaza in Bangladesh will be held on the foreign ministry premises at 11.45am, before the body is taken to his Gulshan home. Amin will be laid to rest at Mirpur graveyard after a second namaz-e-janaza at Azad Mosque in Gulshan. Meanwhile, French foreign minister Bernard Kouchner sent a condolence message through a director of the French foreign ministry to the widow of the ambassador conveying their deep sympathies. On behalf of the French president, Kouchner also sent a condolence letter to foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury. "The French government will arrange a funeral in honour of the late ambassador Ruhul Amin on Jan 7," the foreign ministry said in another statement. Bangladeshis living in Paris will join the namaz-e-janaza in Paris, it said. bdn
